4) Once you have finished these steps, do a gradle rebuild, and run your program. In Jem, do the transaction that generates your report. If you would like to see if reports are being generated, breakpoints are your best friend! 
If you are unsure how to generate a report in JEM, please see the file: TI-1607_Unit_Test.docx in Jira.  

==================================================================================================================================================

5) How to test if reports are being generated:

	1)	Go to PostGresIII
	2)	Go to your database
	3)	Make sure you click refresh
	4)	Inside Schemas, click on tables
	5)	Search for the table that contains your data. For example, if you are using RPAC as your key, you need to search adbrpac.
	6)	After finding the table, click on the SQL symbol on top of the page.
	7)	Run this query:
 		select variable_data_object from adbrpac
 		where AK1_REPORT_ID = 'ESTB'
	8)	 If there is data, then you have succeeded at putting your data into the database.

