 6) Important! If you see this error:
	14:00:27,961 ERROR [stderr] (Thread-27 (ActiveMQ-client-global-threads-317407364)) java.io.InvalidClassException: com.lidp.model.admin.persistence.REPT_ESTB_Extract; local class incompatible: stream classdesc serialVersionUID = -2390401990896385402, local class serialVersionUID = 661058466750954063
	It means that you have changed the REPT_ESTB_Extract or REPT_ESTB_Entry or XML_ESTB_Extract or XML_ESTB_Entry classes, making them incompatible with the current data.
	If you encounter this, you need to delete the data currently in the database. To do this, run this query in pgAdmin III:
	delete from adbrpac
	where AK1_REPORT_ID = 'ESTB'

	Every time you change the extract or entry, you need to run this query or you will get a serialization error!

	BTW: if you get this error:
		Exception: Need to specify class name in environment or system property: java.naming.factory.initial
		Then, you need to delete your current Ti_Client-Handler-Resources and relink it in your Ti_Client_Listener
		If you get any other strange errors with starting JEM, try doing a Gradle refresh on all project folders.

