10) If you encounter an XML problem where it references the object instead of printing the value like this:

<BILL__Notice__Relationship__Area>
	<relationship>I</relationship>
		<clients>
			<BILL__Notice__Relationship__Entry 
			reference="../../../BILL__Notice__Relationship__Area/clients/BILL__Notice__Relationship__Entry"/> //Reference to the first instance of the object
			<BILL__Notice__Relationship__Entry>
			<name>Great Mann</name>
			<addresses>
				<string>Has Address Addresstown AL 12345</string>
			</addresses>
		<rels>I </rels>
		<initObjects>true</initObjects>
	</BILL__Notice__Relationship__Entry>

It can occur when you are trying to reference the same object more than once. For example, if you are going through the same loop of objects for each relationship, 
the XML report will get confused on which values to use, so it will reference out. For instance (APRBDR00 and APRBDL00 from TI-1599):

for (Character clientRel : allClientRelationships)
      {
         BILL_Notice_Relationship_Area tempRelEntries = new BILL_Notice_Relationship_Area();

         for (BILL_Notice_Relationship_Entry myEntry : relEntries) 
         {
            for (char entryRel : myEntry.getRels().toCharArray())
            {
               if (entryRel == clientRel)
               {  
                  tempRelEntries.addClient(myEntry); //The XML report will get confused on which myEntry to use, so it will reference to the first instance of the object.
               }
            }
         }

         tempRelEntries.setRelationship(clientRel);
         reportObj.addRelationshipEntry(tempRelEntries); 




To fix this, I recommend this example solution (APRBDR00 and APRBDL00 from TI-1599):

for (Character clientRel : allClientRelationships)
      {
         BILL_Notice_Relationship_Area tempRelEntries = new BILL_Notice_Relationship_Area();

         for (BILL_Notice_Relationship_Entry myEntry : relEntries) 
         {
            for (char entryRel : myEntry.getRels().toCharArray())
            {
               if (entryRel == clientRel)
               {
                  BILL_Notice_Relationship_Entry tempClient = new BILL_Notice_Relationship_Entry(); //Create a temporary object
                  tempClient.setName(myEntry.getName()); //set that object to the first value (e.g.name) 
                  
                  for (String address: myEntry.getAddresses())
                  {
                     tempClient.addAddress(address); //second value
                  }
                  
                  tempRelEntries.addClient(tempClient);
               }
            }
         }

         tempRelEntries.setRelationship(clientRel);
         reportObj.addRelationshipEntry(tempRelEntries);

